### `train.py` — PPO metrics (issue 10)

Added `_LogCapture` class injected into `model.logger.output_formats`. SB3 calls `logger.dump()` after each training update (and clears `name_to_value` at that point), so `_on_step` could never see the values. `_LogCapture.write()` is called *during* `dump()`, caching `train/*` metrics into `self._log_capture` before the clear. `_on_step` now reads from that persistent dict.
